description:
Rename the Drizzle schema file and update its TypeScript exports while keeping the actual SQLite table names unchanged.

## File Rename

Rename `packages/db/src/schema/pulse.ts` to `packages/db/src/schema/tasks.ts`.

## Code Changes in `packages/db/src/schema/tasks.ts`

The `sqliteTable()` calls keep their string table names (`'pulse_schedules'` and `'pulse_runs'`), but the TypeScript export names and TSDoc change:

```typescript
import { sqliteTable, text, integer } from 'drizzle-orm/sqlite-core';

/** Task definitions cached from .md files. Internal table name retained for migration simplicity. */
export const pulseSchedules = sqliteTable('pulse_schedules', {
  // ... all existing columns unchanged ...
});

/** Execution history for task runs. Internal table name retained for migration simplicity. */
export const pulseRuns = sqliteTable('pulse_runs', {
  // ... all existing columns unchanged ...
});
```

Note: The TypeScript variable names `pulseSchedules` and `pulseRuns` are kept for now to avoid a massive Drizzle query refactor across the server. They will reference the same tables. The Drizzle variable names can be cleaned up later.

## Update barrel export

Update `packages/db/src/schema/index.ts` (or wherever `pulse.ts` is imported) to import from `./tasks.ts` instead of `./pulse.ts`.

Search for all imports of `@dorkos/db/schema/pulse` or `../schema/pulse` across the codebase and update them to `@dorkos/db/schema/tasks` or `../schema/tasks`.

## Acceptance Criteria
- `packages/db/src/schema/pulse.ts` no longer exists
- `packages/db/src/schema/tasks.ts` exists with the same content (updated TSDoc comments)
- All imports updated to reference the new path
- SQLite table names remain `pulse_schedules` and `pulse_runs` in the `sqliteTable()` calls
- `pnpm typecheck` passes for `@dorkos/db`
